AD  - Rheinisch-Westfälische Technische Hochschule Aachen, Aachen, Germany
AB  - In factory planning, the interoperability problem poses high demands to information technology. The emerging concept of the digital twin, which refers to a coupled virtual representation of an asset, currently represents a promising approach to integrating planning information, methods, and tools. However, its exact definition and role in factory planning as well as the current development and implementation status needs clarification. Therefore, this paper provides an overview of the current state by systematically reviewing the literature on digital factory twins and their potential applications in factory planning. The findings highlight the potential of integrated information systems for creating digital factory twins and the challenges in defining modeling standards and reference architectures. Further, simulation capabilities are frequently leveraged by real-time data interfaces. Finally, we identify opportunities and directions for further research to aid the industrial adoption of digital factory twins. © 2024 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.
