AD  - Dolphin Oilfield Equipment Services Company LLC, Department of Engineering, Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates
AB  - Predictive maintenance plays a crucial role in enhancing heat exchanger efficiency by minimizing fouling-related performance degradation. This systematic literature review examines digital twin models for accurately predicting fouling and optimizing maintenance schedules in heat exchangers. The review covers recent research exploring the application of various digital twin models in predicting fouling in different industries. It also covers how much efficiency can be achieved by implementing prediction-based maintenance. The analysis of existing literature shows that the digital twin models are up to 99% accurate in predicting fouling, remaining useful life (RUL), and other performance parameters. Synthesis of the literature review also reveals that the implementation of predictive maintenance enhances operational efficiency, reducing the cost of maintenance and contributing to a sustainable and resource-optimized future for industries. The research aims to provide practical recommendations for businesses to implement digital twin models effectively in order to enhance heat exchanger efficiency and reduce maintenance costs. Moreover, this review identifies the need for further research to develop a comprehensive digital twin model tailored for predictive maintenance, calibrated using real-world data and scenarios. © 2023 Elsevier B.V., All rights reserved.
